Multiomic regulatory network analysis via txRegQuery (formerly mongoDrillConductor)

BJ Stubbs, Shweta Gopaulakrishnan, Vince Carey, Peter Castaldi Channing Division of Network Medicine, Brigham and Womens Hospital

July 26, 2017

Lee, Rinaldi et al. Science 2002: TxRegNet for S. cerevisiae

  • Condition/phenotype: stage \(G_1, S, G_2, M\), budding

  • Blue boxes: upregulated genes

  • Ovals/Arcs: transcription factors and their periods of influence

Maurano, Humbert et al. Science 2012: Common (human) disease network

  • Disease:DNA GWAS SNPs in FIMO-identified binding sites

  • Sequence for motif finding: hg19-alt all SNP sites coded as alternate allele , with GWAS SNPs that disrupt FIMO-identified binding sites (BSgenome has a method for SNP-injection)

  • New challenge: from sequence-derived TFBS, epigenomically defined regulatory regions (tissue-specific), tissue-specific (GTEX) eQTL, derive regulatory networks to help interpret local COPD GWAS
